Package com.intellij.openapi.fileEditor

Interface FileEditorProvider

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AsyncFileEditorProvider, DefaultPlatformFileEditorProvider
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EditorConfigEditorProvider, LargeFileEditorProvider, LargeFileEditorProvider, MarkdownPreviewFileEditorProvider, MarkdownSplitEditorProvider, PerspectiveFileEditorProvider, PsiAwareTextEditorProvider, ResourceBundleEditorProvider, RestSplitEditorProvider, SceneBuilderEditorProvider, SplitTextEditorProvider, TerminalSessionEditorProvider, TextEditorProvider, UIFormEditorProvider, WeighedFileEditorProvider

    public interface FileEditorProvider
    Should be registered via EP_FILE_EDITOR_PROVIDER.
    See Also:
    DumbAware

    • Method Detail

      • accept

        boolean accept(Project project,
               VirtualFile file)
        Method is expected to run fast.
        Parameters:
        file - file to be tested for acceptance.
        Returns:
        true if provider can create valid editor for the specified file.

      • createEditor

        FileEditor createEditor(Project project,
                        VirtualFile file)
        Creates editor for the specified file.

        This method is called only if the provider has accepted this file (i.e. method accept(Project, VirtualFile) returned true). The provider should return only valid editor.

        Returns:
        created editor for specified file.

      • disposeEditor

        default void disposeEditor(FileEditor editor)
        Disposes the specified editor. It is guaranteed that this method is invoked only for editors created with this provider.
        Parameters:
        editor - editor to be disposed.

      • readState

        default FileEditorState readState(Element sourceElement,
                                  Project project,
                                  VirtualFile file)
        Deserialize state from the specified sourceElement.

      • writeState

        default void writeState(FileEditorState state,
                        Project project,
                        Element targetElement)
        Serializes state into the specified targetElement.

      • getEditorTypeId

        java.lang.String getEditorTypeId()
        Returns:
        id of type of the editors created with this FileEditorProvider. Each FileEditorProvider should have unique nonnull id. The id is used for saving/loading of EditorStates.

      • getPolicy

        FileEditorPolicy getPolicy()
        Returns:
        policy that specifies how editor created via this provider should be opened.
        See Also:
        FileEditorPolicy.NONE, FileEditorPolicy.HIDE_DEFAULT_EDITOR, FileEditorPolicy.PLACE_BEFORE_DEFAULT_EDITOR
